{{more footnotes|date=October 2012}}
'''Barua Buddhist monks''' are monks from the [[Barua (Bangladesh)|Barua]] community in Bangladesh. Since ancient times, they have guided the Barua community on [[Buddhist philosophy]]. They practice their Buddhist faith in the [[Chittagong Hill Tracts]] and surrounding areas. Their valuable contributions are respected by all Baruas.
