'''David Bowen''' (11 December 1774 – 18 November 1853) was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] [[Baptists|Baptist]] minister. He was born in [[Felinfoel]], [[Carmarthenshire]]. In 1797 he was baptised at the local church; he began preaching at that same church in 1798. In 1806 he was ordained by Titus Lewis and Joshua Watkins and was appointed as joint-minister with Daniel Davies. In 1831 the congregation of the newly formed [[Zion Baptist Chapel, Llanelli|Capel Seion]] in [[Llanelli]] chose him to be its pastor, a position he held until his death in 1853.<ref>{{cite web|title=David Bowen|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s3-BOWE-DAV-1774.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref>

