'''Mantra Gopya''' is a [[Kannada language]] text written by [[Veerashaiva]] saint and mystic [[Allama Prabhu]].<ref>{{cite book |title=A handbook of Vīraśaivism |year=1979 |authors= Sivalingayya Channabasavayya Nandimath, Ramendra Nath Nandi |isbn=0896840530 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x2E9AAAAIAAJ&q=Mantra+Gopya+allama |page=16}}</ref> It forms an important part of [[Veerashaiva]] scriptures.<ref>{{cite book |title=Community Dominance and Political Modernisation: The Lingayats |year=2002 |author= Shankaragouda Hanamantagouda Patil |isbn=8170998670 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R84n-Wv1S-8C&pg=PA20 |page=20}}</ref>
